1. Find a bank that you want to rob.
2. Research the bank's security measures to determine the best way to enter the bank undetected.
3. Plan your escape route.
4. Obtain a firearm, preferably a handgun, if you do not have one already.
5. Wear clothing that allows for easy movement and concealment of the firearm.
6. Enter the bank with the firearm concealed.
7. Approach the teller and demand money.
8. Keep your firearm concealed and do not point it at anyone unless necessary.
9. Take as much money as you can without drawing attention to yourself.
10. Exit the bank quickly and follow your escape route.
11. If you are caught by security or law enforcement, remain calm and cooperate.